  {"a":"aurora_mid","b":"yasuo","win":["Aurora","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Your Q Twin Drift poke keeps Yasuo off balance since he needs to walk into your range to get value from Steel Tempest, and E The Weirding punishes any wave-clear attempt with Wind Wall down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His Last Breath knock-up threat requires a knock-up setup first, and Between Worlds lets you avoid getting caught out by his all-in the moment he commits to a dash."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Lost Chapter spike keeps your poke damage ahead of his snowballing crit scaling before he completes a full build."},{"when":"Late","text":"Your kiting and burst still outclass his all-in dive potential since Between Worlds gives you an escape from his gap-close tools even once he's fully itemized."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke from range and punish his dash cooldown windows before he closes distance","Bait Wind Wall with a delayed cast rather than your main combo","Track his knock-up setups since his all-in relies entirely on a landed CC chain"],"foe":["Wind Wall your key poke or burst spell to neutralize your damage window","Land a knock-up combo with jungler help to force a guaranteed all-in","Snowball crit items to out-scale your damage into the late game"]},"early":"You control the level 1-2 lane phase since Yasuo has to walk into melee range to threaten you, letting your Q Twin Drift poke punish every approach attempt without much risk.","mid":"Through levels 3 to 6 you maintain the lead as his all-in still requires a landed knock-up to be safe, and your Between Worlds dodge tool means his ultimate arrival doesn't create the guaranteed kill window he wants.","late":"You keep the edge into the late game and beyond because your escape and burst combo continues to outpace his all-in potential, letting you punish his engages even as he scales into a stronger crit-based build.","whys":["Your ranged poke punishes his need to walk into melee range from the start","You continue winning trades as his all-in still lacks a reliable setup tool","Your poke keeps outpacing his damage through the level 3 skirmish window","Your ranged pressure holds through levels 4-5 despite his growing threat level","Your dodge tool denies his knock-up-reliant all-in the moment he hits 6","Your item spike keeps your damage ahead of his crit-scaling curve","Your kiting and escape tools continue to outclass his all-in dive even late"]},
  {"a":"aurora_mid","b":"yone","win":["Aurora","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora","Yone","Aurora"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Your Q Twin Drift poke plus E slow chunks Yone every time he tries to walk up for a Q3 knockup, and he has no ranged answer until he's fully committed to the dash-in."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Yone hits 6 first-ish in trades where he's pushed, and his Ult can catch you mid-cast if you overextend on a Q read — respect the first all-in window even though your R keeps you safer than most mages."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Riftmaker/Shadowflame timings let you poke from Twin Drift range all day; Yone still needs to close the gap through your E zone, so item power widens your lead."},{"when":"Late","text":"In 2+ item teamfights your R Between Worlds pulls you out of his Q3/R combo entirely, and your zone control from E denies him the flank angles Yone needs to be relevant."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke with Q Twin Drift from max range before he can walk up","Hold E Weirding to punish his Q3 dash-in windup, not just for damage","Bait his Q1/Q2 into minions so his knockup threat resets","Track his ult charge and pre-position R Between Worlds before he all-ins"],"foe":["Farm safely with Q1/Q2 through minions until level 6","Wait for you to overextend chasing wave or roam value","All-in immediately off his Level 6 spike before you can react","Use his passive shield to tank your poke through an engage"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are yours outright — Yone has no ranged tool to fight your Q Twin Drift poke, so every time he pushes to farm you punish him with Q+E and back off before his Q3 dash can land. He's forced into passive last-hitting through your zone, which costs him CS and tempo he badly needs pre-6.","mid":"Levels 3-5 stay in your favor as your poke compounds and your E slow means his Q3 all-in windup gets punished before it connects — but the moment Yone hits Level 6 his Mounting Doom ult adds a hard-engage tool that can catch you out if you're greedy with Q resets, so play the level 6 window with your R held in reserve rather than committed to poke.","late":"With items and by 2+ purchases you're fully back in control — Riftmaker or Shadowflame scaling makes your poke lethal from range Yone can't close safely, and your R Between Worlds gives you a hard out from his Q3/R all-in combo that he doesn't have an answer to; play for poke-and-disengage, not extended trades, and this matchup snowballs hard in your favor.","whys":["Aurora's ranged Q poke overwhelms Yone's melee farming pattern with no counter-poke available.","Continued poke pressure plus E's slow keeps Yone off his dash timing and behind on CS.","Same pattern holds — Yone still lacks tools to close the gap safely against sustained ranged pressure.","Poke advantage compounds through mid-game as Yone's all-in windows keep getting punished pre-emptively.","Yone's ult grants a genuine hard-engage burst window that can catch Aurora if she overcommits to poke.","Aurora's ranged poke returns to dominance as the ult cooldown passes and no all-in landed.","Item power plus R's escape utility make Aurora untouchable to Yone's combo in teamfights."]},
  {"a":"aurora_mid","b":"zed","win":["Aurora","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora","Zed","Aurora"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Zed's Shadow poke is weak into your Q Twin Drift range, and your E Weirding punishes any Q3 shuriken-return dash he tries before he has Ult, so he's stuck farming under tower most of levels 3-5."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Zed's Death Mark spike is real and sudden — he can shadow-swap in from fog or a bush and burst you before your R Between Worlds is ready to bail, so this is genuinely his window, not yours."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once you have your first burst item back online, your poke-and-punish pattern reasserts itself and Zed's all-in outside his ult cooldown does nothing against your kit."},{"when":"Late","text":"By 2+ items your R Between Worlds gives you a clean dodge for his Death Mark reveal-burst combo, and your ranged zone denies him the Shadow-dash approach entirely — he's forced to wait for picks elsewhere."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke with Q Twin Drift and back off before his shadow range","Never stand still near brush once he's Level 6 — vision matters more than trades here","Save R Between Worlds to slip out of his Death Mark reveal, not for extra damage","Punish his mana-less all-ins with E's slow after he shadow-dashes in"],"foe":["Farm passively with shadows behind minions pre-6","Look for a shadow-swap engage from brush or fog right at Level 6","All-in immediately during his ult window before you can react","Roam off-lane rather than force a losing trade pre-ult"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 you're clearly ahead — Zed's shadow-based poke can't match Q Twin Drift at range, and any shadow-dash approach walks straight into your E slow, so he's forced into a passive farming pattern that costs him tempo and sets up nothing.","mid":"That advantage holds through levels 3-5, but the second Zed hits Level 6 the entire dynamic flips: Death Mark is a real burst threat that can come from a shadow placed in fog or brush, catching you before your R is up to escape — treat this level exactly like a landmine and play with vision and spacing, not greed.","late":"Once your first item lands you're back in firm control, and by 2+ items your R Between Worlds is a clean answer to his ult reveal-burst — hold it specifically for that combo rather than for damage, and your ranged zone keeps him from ever finding a safe all-in angle again.","whys":["Aurora's ranged poke shuts down Zed's melee shadow-farming with no counter available pre-6.","Same dynamic continues — Zed has no way to close distance safely against sustained poke and slow.","Poke advantage compounds; Zed remains stuck behind minions with no all-in tool yet.","Aurora keeps building lead through levels 4-5 as Zed's ult is still on cooldown or not yet taken.","Zed's Death Mark grants a real burst-engage window from stealth that can kill Aurora before her escape is ready.","Aurora's poke and zone control return to dominance once the ult threat is spent or baited out.","Item power plus R's dodge for Death Mark's reveal make Aurora safe and dominant in extended play."]},
  {"a":"aurora_mid","b":"ziggs","win":["Ziggs","Ziggs","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ziggs' Bouncing Bomb outranges Q Twin Drift at levels 1-2, but once you have E Weirding available to close distance and punish his cooldowns, you start winning the trade window he can't escape."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Neither ult changes the lane fight directly here — Mega Inferno Bomb is a wave/turret tool more than a duel threat, so your Level 6 spike is about raw stat growth and W utility, not a burst combo."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first burst item lets you punish Ziggs' short-range poke pattern hard — he has zero escape besides Satchel Charge, and once that's on cooldown you can all-in freely."},{"when":"Late","text":"By 2+ items you fully close the range gap with E's dash-adjacent mobility, and Ziggs' immobility becomes a liability in skirmishes and objective fights where you can just walk him down."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive levels 1-2 passively — don't contest bomb trades you can't win","Use E Weirding's mobility to close the gap once you have Q and E both up","Track Satchel Charge cooldown before committing to an all-in","Push waves fast late so Ziggs can't safely poke from max range"],"foe":["Poke relentlessly from max Bouncing Bomb range levels 1-2","Zone you off CS using bomb-minion clears","Play safe and kite once you hit Level 3 and Aurora can close distance","Use Mega Inferno Bomb for wave clear and turret pressure, not dueling"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are rough — Ziggs' Bouncing Bomb range and damage outclass your early Q Twin Drift, and he'll poke you off CS repeatedly with no way for you to punish since he simply won't be in E range; play passive, take farm through minions, and don't contest bomb trades you can't win.","mid":"The moment you unlock Q and E together around level 3, the matchup flips hard — E Weirding gives you the mobility to actually close his range advantage, and once you're in his face his short-ranged kit and lack of true escape (Satchel Charge aside) mean you win nearly every trade from here through his own Level 6 spike, which does nothing to change the duel.","late":"By first item and especially at 2+ items you're fully in control: Ziggs has no way to kite an ability-haste, mobility-boosted Aurora, and his ult is a wave/tower tool rather than a way to save himself in a skirmish — push him under tower, force cooldowns, and take every fight he can't run from.","whys":["Ziggs' longer Bouncing Bomb range lets him poke Aurora for free before she has E's gap-close online.","Same range disadvantage persists — Aurora still lacks the tools to punish his poke safely.","Once Aurora has Q and E together she closes the gap and wins the trade decisively.","Aurora's mobility and burst continue to dominate as Ziggs has no scaling answer to close-range fights.","Neither champion's ultimate is a duel-winning tool here, so the lane stays on Aurora's established lead.","Aurora's gap-close and burst combo keep overwhelming Ziggs' immobile poke kit.","Item power widens Aurora's mobility gap further, letting her run down an immobile Ziggs at will."]},
  {"a":"aurora_mid","b":"zoe","win":["Zoe","Zoe","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Zoe's Spell Thief'd summoner spells and bubble poke are dangerous early, but once you hit Level 3 your own Q Twin Drift range and E's slow start matching her burst potential trade-for-trade."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Neither ult flips the lane outright — Zoe's Portal Jump-R combo is more a roam/pick tool than an in-lane duel-winner against your ranged kit, so your steady stat growth keeps compounding."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With your first burst item, you out-trade Zoe's short burst windows reliably since she has no sustained pressure once her combo is on cooldown."},{"when":"Late","text":"By 2+ items your R Between Worlds gives you a safe out from her Sleepy Trouble Bubble engage attempts, and your consistent poke outpaces her all-in-or-nothing burst pattern."}],"wants":{"you":["Play cautious around unwarded bushes pre-6 — her bubble one-shot potential is real","Don't waste mana trying to out-poke her landed sleepy bubble combo","Start trading confidently in lane once you're Level 3 with Q and E up","Hold R Between Worlds as an escape from her bubble-into-burst all-in"],"foe":["Land Sleepy Trouble Bubble from a bush for a free burst combo pre-6","Steal a flash or exhaust off your summoners with Spell Thief","Poke safely with Q Paddle Star before you can trade back","Look for pick potential with Portal Jump rather than a straight fight"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favor Zoe outright — her bubble-into-burst combo threatens a real kill if she lands Sleepy Trouble Bubble from brush, and her Q poke chips you down safely at a range you can't yet answer, so play cautious, ward the flanks, and don't feed her a stolen summoner spell.","mid":"Once you hit Level 3 with Q and E both up, the matchup evens out and then tilts your way — your own poke and slow start matching her burst threat for threat, and by Level 6 neither ultimate changes the fundamental trade since her Portal Jump-R is built more for roaming and picks than dueling a ranged mage who can now punish her cooldowns.","late":"With your first item and beyond you're clearly ahead — Zoe's damage is entirely burst-window dependent and falls off hard once her combo is spent, while your steady poke and R Between Worlds (held specifically to dodge a bubble-into-burst attempt) let you out-trade and out-scale her into every subsequent fight.","whys":["Zoe's bubble-into-burst combo from stealth threatens a real early kill Aurora can't yet answer.","Zoe's safe poke range and burst combo continue to outclass Aurora's still-developing kit at these levels.","Aurora's Q and E come online together and start matching Zoe's burst threat for threat.","Aurora's consistent poke and trade potential keep compounding as Zoe's combo remains cooldown-gated.","Neither ultimate is a duel-winner here, so Aurora's established mid-game lead simply continues.","Aurora's steady damage and survivability options keep outpacing Zoe's spent burst windows.","Item scaling plus R's escape from bubble engages make Aurora clearly favored in extended play."]}
